Energy:        [E] GeV
Circumference: [C] m

Phase 1 — Baseline
  Tunes:          nu_x = ..., nu_y = ...
  Chromaticities: xi_x = ..., xi_y = ...
  Beta extrema:   beta_x_max = ... m, beta_y_max = ... m
  Status:         OK

Phase 2 — Working Point
  Nearest critical: [resonance] at d = ...
  Nearest dangerous: [resonance] at d = ...
  Status:           GREEN / YELLOW / RED

Phase 3 — Corrections Applied
  Tune adjustment:       [before] → [after] (or "not needed")
  Chromaticity correction: [before] → [after] (or "not needed")

Phase 4 — Verification
  Dynamic aperture:  [area] mm²
  Frequency map:     [clean / concerning regions noted]

Overall: HEALTHY / NEEDS ATTENTION / CRITICAL
===
```

## Optics Comparison (use after any modification)

When comparing optics before/after a change, deep-copy the ring first:

```python
import copy
baseline = copy.deepcopy(ring)
ld0_base, rd_base, ld_base = at.get_optics(
    baseline, refpts=range(len(baseline) + 1), get_chrom=True
)
```

After applying a modification, compute modified optics and create an overlay
plot with dashed lines for baseline and solid for modified. Print a comparison
table of tunes, chromaticities, and beta extrema.

## Decision Tree

```
Load & Compute Optics
  |
  +-- Optics broken (NaN, unstable) --> STOP, report critical failure
  |
  +-- Optics OK --> Working Point Analysis
  |     |
  |     +-- CRITICAL resonance d < 0.01
  |     |     --> Suggest tune adjustment --> fit_tune --> re-analyze --> verify
  |     |
  |     +-- DANGEROUS resonance d < 0.02
  |     |     --> Warn, offer tune adjustment
  |     |
  |     +-- All clear (d > 0.03)
  |           --> Report healthy
  |
  +-- Chromaticity Check
  |     +-- Large negative --> offer fit_chrom
  |     +-- Reasonable --> OK
  |
  +-- Verification (if changes made)
  |     +-- Dynamic aperture
  |     +-- Frequency map
  |
  +-- Final Summary
```
